subSubSection.paragraph:
Greater Marmoset Rat (
H. longicaudatus
) and similar in sizeto the Lesser Marmoset Rat (
H. delacouri
) but with longer tail. Pelage is dense and soft, with marked difference between grayish brown dorsum (seemingly more gray on rump) and white venter. Tail is covered with long hairs on distal part, completely black, and 116% of head-body length. Hallux offoot is fully opposable and has nail instead ofclaw. Ears are small and rounded. Skull has short and
